  "prompt": "How would you word \"damas\" and \"chambelanes\" for an english Quinceanera invitation?",
  "response": "For an English Quincea\u00f1era invitation, \"damas\" and \"chambelanes\" can be translated to \"maids\" and \"chamberlains,\" respectively, or more commonly, \"court of honor\" for both terms collectively. Here\u2019s a phrasing you might use:\n\n---\n\n**Join us for [Name]'s Quincea\u00f1era**\n\nWith her Maids and Chamberlains\n\nor\n\nWith her Court of Honor\n\n---\n\nThis translation conveys the traditional roles within the celebration while keeping the invitation elegant and understandable for an English-speaking audience.",
